Section 1:
Act 588 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S3/31/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 153
4
5 By: Senator J. Dotson
6 By: Representative Warren
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING VARIOUS PROVISIONS
10 OF TITLE 24 OF THE ARKANSAS CODE; TO AMEND THE LAW
11 REGARDING THE PAYMENT OF RETIREMENT BENEFITS TO
12 VARIOUS CITY OFFICIALS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING VARIOUS
17 PROVISIONS OF TITLE 24 OF THE ARKANSAS
18 CODE; AND TO AMEND THE LAW REGARDING THE
19 PAYMENT OF RETIREMENT BENEFITS TO
20 VARIOUS CITY OFFICIALS.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 24-12-120(c), concerning payment of
25 retirement benefits to city attorneys in cities of the first class and cities
26 of the second class, is amended to read as follows:
27 (c) All payments of retirement benefits under this section shall be
28 payable monthly and shall be paid from the general funds of by the city.
29
30 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 24-12-121(b)(2), concerning retirement
31 payments to city clerks and clerk-treasurers, is amended to read as follows:
32 (2) The retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its
33 general fund account.
34
35 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 24-12-122(b)(2), concerning retirement
36 payments to deputy city clerks, is amended to read as follows:
*LJH102*
03-31-2025 10:28:55 LJH102
As Engrossed: S3/31/25 SB153
1 (2) The retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its
2 general fund account when appropriated for that purpose by the governing body
3 of the city.
4
5 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code § 24-12-123(a)(2), concerning retirement
6 payments to mayors of cities of the first class, is amended to read as
7 follows:
8 (2) The retirement payments shall be paid monthly and shall be
9 paid from the city general fund by the city.
10
11 SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 24-12-125(b)(2), concerning retirement
12 payments to treasurers of cities of the first class, is amended to read as
13 follows:
14 (2) Upon approval by the governing body of the city, the
15 retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its general fund account.
16
17 SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 24-12-127(b)(2), concerning retirement
18 payments to recorder-treasurers and city treasurers of cities of the second
19 class, is amended to read as follows:
20 (2) The retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its
21 general fund account.
22
23 /s/J. Dotson
